The paper discusses deep learning systems and their vulnerabilities, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on the robustness of these systems, which is a topic of interest in the sub-categories of computer security (cs.CR) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper proposes a testing criteria for DL systems, which falls under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE).
